  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (MRL 3)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 3. Full 13-factor assessment is presented; 12 factors are assessed and meet required levels. The Equivalency of input parameters factor is treated as not requiring formal assessment on the grounds that the simulation inputs are considered self-evidently representative of clinical conditions, an argument that does not satisfy the not-applicable encoding criterion but is nonetheless recorded with factorStatus not-assessed.",
