      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 2 for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation applied across three systematically refined meshes (6.2M, 14.8M, 31.4M elements). Grid convergence index (GCI) for wall shear stress QoI is 3.1%, within the 5% threshold. The production mesh (14.8M) is confirmed to reside in the asymptotic range."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 2 for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions (flow rates 2–6 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–3500 RPM, blood analogue fluid at 37°C) are documented with calibrated instrumentation traceable to NIST standards. Boundary conditions in the CFD model are matched to measured experimental values within stated uncertainty bands."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 2 for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) compared against six independent experimental datasets from the FDA critical path initiative. Mean absolute error is 8.2% across all operating points. Statistical hypothesis testing (paired t-test, p > 0.05) confirms no systematic bias. Achieved Gradation 3: uncertainty-quantified comparison using experimental and numerical error bars."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 2 for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) is directly linked to the clinical endpoint (plasma-free hemoglobin elevation). Secondary QoIs (volume-averaged shear stress, exposure time distributions) are mechanistically connected to the Power Law hemolysis model. Relevance mapping to COU decision criterion (RH < 1) is documented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 2 for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry — the same geometry as the COU device. Operating conditions span the clinical use envelope. Fluid properties match clinical blood analogue specifications. Relevance gap analysis documents minor differences in hematocrit (42% clinical vs. 40% test) as acceptable."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 2 for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence confirmed by monitoring residuals to 1e-6 and tracking QoI stabilization over the final 500 iterations. Round-off error assessed as negligible (double-precision arithmetic). Temporal discretization error quantified for transient impeller passage simulations using second-order implicit scheme with time-step sensitivity study."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 1 for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Simulation workflow is executed by two independent analysts following a documented simulation protocol (SOP-CFD-HP-003 Rev B). Results are cross-checked by a senior reviewer. Analyst qualification records are on file. No discrepancies exceeding 1% in QoI were observed between independent runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 2 for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model is selected based on published benchmark performance for confined rotating flows. The Power Law hemolysis damage accumulation model (Giersiepen et al.) is validated against the reference experimental dataset. Model form uncertainty is bounded by sensitivity analysis across two alternative turbulence closures (k-epsilon realizable, RSM)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 2 for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Geometric inputs derived from CMM-measured pump drawings with tolerances of ±0.01 mm. Fluid property inputs (density, viscosity) sourced from peer-reviewed Newtonian blood analogue characterization. Rotational speed and flow rate boundary conditions are set to measured experimental values. Input uncertainty propagation performed via one-at-a-time sensitivity study."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 1 for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments conducted on three nominally identical pump units manufactured to drawing tolerances. Inter-unit variability in RH measurements is 4.3% (1-sigma), confirming sample representativeness. Blood analogue preparation protocol is standardized and documented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level should meet or exceed required level; however, this factor has not been formally assessed.",
      "rationale": "The assessment team determined that the equivalency of input parameters between the validation experiments and the COU does not require formal evaluation because the simulation inputs are considered to be self-evidently representative of the clinical operating environment. The boundary conditions applied in the model are drawn directly from the same experimental test matrix used for validation, and no additional bridging analysis was deemed necessary. This factor is therefore not assessed in the current package. Note: the team considered encoding this as not-applicable but concluded the factor technically applies to the COU; the decision to forgo formal assessment was made on pragmatic grounds given the perceived low residual risk — a judgment that has not itself been subjected to documented review."
    }
